'''7-Zip''' is an [[Free software|free]] [[open source]] [[file archiver]] designed originally for [[Microsoft Windows]], and later made available to other computer [[operating system]]s. In the form of [[p7zip]], the command-line version of 7-Zip has been ported for use on [[Unix-like]] systems such as [[GNU]]/[[Linux]], [[Berkeley Software Distribution|BSD]], and [[Mac OS X]] as well as [[AmigaOS]]. It is also compatible with DOS via either a DOS port, or by using the [[HX DOS Extender|HX-DOS]] extender to run the Windows command-line version.
